{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/convert_to_lava", "tags": "viscousfluids"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Lava from Object"], "extent": [51, 72]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a lava object from geometry."], "extent": [72, 117]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [117, 132], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool turns a geometry object into a particle fluid with defaults appropriate for simulating lava. It also applies a lava shader to the result of the simulation. You would typically use this tool if you want an object made from lava which will cool off and harden over time."], "extent": [132, 413]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [413, 419], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The difference between this tool and ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/meltobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Melt Object"], "fullpath": "/shelf/meltobject"}, " is that this tool assigns a shader to get a basic glowing lava look, while ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/meltobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Melt Object"], "fullpath": "/shelf/meltobject"}, " doesn\u2019t apply any shader. "], "extent": [419, 628]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Lava from Object"], "extent": [628, 657], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create a geometry object to be converted into lava."], "extent": [657, 713]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/convert_to_lava", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/convert_to_lava"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Lava from Object"]}, " tool on the Viscous Fluids tab. "], "extent": [713, 808], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/flipobject", "type": "link", "text": ["FLIP Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/flipobject"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " help pages."], "extent": [808, 965]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/lavafromobject.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [965, 1007]}, {"level": 3, "id": "tips", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [16, 33], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": [" Change how quickly the objects starts to melt"], "role": "item", "extent": [33, 92], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Modify the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Temperature"]}, " parameter on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Physical"]}, " tab of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/flipobject", "type": "link", "text": ["FLIP Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/flipobject"}, ". This parameter sets the initial temperature of the object. The default value is 0.5, which will cause it to melt immediately, since the object starts off quite warm. A higher value will give you very hot, free-flowing liquid which cools over time and a lower value would give you cool, highly viscous fluid that heats up and melts."], "extent": [92, 544]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": [" Change the look of the fluid"], "role": "item", "extent": [544, 585], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Adjust the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Minimum/Maximum Viscosity"]}, " parameters on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " node. A value of 100,000 is very stiff, which should retain it\u2019s shape, and a value of 0 is completely liquid, like water."], "extent": [585, 839]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": [" Control how quickly a hot temperature will cool off"], "role": "item", "extent": [839, 903], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Modify the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Outer/Inner Cooling Rate"]}, " parameters on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " node. The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Outer Cooling Rate"]}, " refers to the rate of change on the surface of the object, while the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Inner Cooling Rate"]}, " refers to how fast the temperature changes inside the fluid. Generally, the inner cooling should be lower than the outer, since the inside of the object is insulated and retains more heat, as opposed to the exterior which loses heat more quickly due to the surrounding air."], "extent": [903, 1422]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}], "title": ["Lava from Object"], "summary": ["Creates a lava object from geometry."], "included": ["/shelf/lava_tips"]}